### Comments in Rust

Rust supports several styles of comments for different purposes.

---

### Comment Types

| Type | Syntax | Purpose |
|------|--------|---------|
| Line comment | `//` | Single-line notes |
| Block comment | `/* ... */` | Multi-line notes |
| Doc comment | `///` | Documentation for items |
| Module doc | `//!` | Documentation for the parent item |

---

### Usage Examples

```rust
// This is a line comment

/*
This is a block comment
that spans multiple lines
*/

/// Adds two numbers together
///
/// # Examples
/// ```
/// let result = add(2, 3);
/// assert_eq!(result, 5);
/// ```
fn add(a: i32, b: i32) -> i32 {
    a + b
}

//! This module contains utility functions
```

> **Key Point:** Use `///` for public API documentation that gets rendered by `rustdoc`. These support Markdown and code examples that are tested via `cargo test`.

codeExample:
fn main() {
    // This is a single-line comment
    let x = 5; // inline comment

    /* Block comments
       can span multiple lines */
    let y = 10;

    println!("x = {}, y = {}", x, y);
}
